---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const projects = [
  {
    name: "zerobrew",
    url: "https://github.com/lucasgelfond/zerobrew",
    description: "optimized client and alternative for homebrew",
    image: "https://opengraph.githubassets.com/1/lucasgelfond/zerobrew"
  },
  {
    name: "nmrs",
    url: "https://github.com/cachebag/nmrs",
    description: "rust bindings for NetworkManager + Wayland-compatible GUI",
    image: "https://opengraph.githubassets.com/1/cachebag/nmrs"
  },
  {
    name: "payme",
    url: "https://github.com/cachebag/payme",
    description: "personal finance tracker built for my homelab",
    image: "https://opengraph.githubassets.com/1/cachebag/payme"
  }
];

const contributions = [
  {
    name: "rustup",
    url: "https://github.com/rust-lang/rustup",
    description: "The Rust toolchain installer",
    image: "https://opengraph.githubassets.com/1/rust-lang/rustup"
  },
  {
    name: "zbus",
    url: "https://github.com/z-galaxy/zbus",
    description: "A Rust API for D-Bus communication",
    image: "https://opengraph.githubassets.com/1/z-galaxy/zbus",
  }
];
---

<Layout title="software | akrm al-hakimi">
  <h1>software</h1>

  <p>
    i've been fortunate enough to work on a nice selection of software, mainly built in rust, that i both own and contribute to/maintain.
    while my professional work currently is primarily in go, OSS in rust is my passion. i believe the future of software built with rust is exceptionally promising.
  </p>

  <p>
    i joined the <a href="https://github.com/lucasgelfond/zerobrew" target="_blank">zerobrew</a> project in january 2026
    and helped ramp up the project to where it is today. some of the notable things we're working on there are: 

    <ul>
      <li>CDN: we'd like to eventually build our packages on a dedicated CDN to further the perf/speed gains we've seen with using rust</li>
      <li>intel: currently we have a <a href="https://github.com/lucasgelfond/zerobrew/issues/286" target="_blank">huge bottleneck</a> around building some packages for intel as well as a reliable CI workflow for it</li>
      <li>extended cask support: we're working on extending the cask support to include more packages, most notably, desktop applications such as claude code desktop or ghostty, for example</li>
    </ul>
  </p>

  <p>
    ...among many other things, we're incredibly excited about the future of zerobrew and the impact it can have on both the rust community and the vast ecosystem of package managers.
  </p>

  <p>
    beyond the new and exciting work i've done with zerobrew, i've also had a lot of fun contributing to <a href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rustup" target="_blank">rustup</a>, as well as working on some of my own projects and the dependencies i rely on for them.
    <a href="https://github.com/cachebag/nmrs" target="_blank">nmrs</a> is a project i've been working on for a while now; it is a set of rust bindings for NetworkManager over D-Bus.
    by extension, i've also contributed a fairly great deal to zbus <a href="https://github.com/z-galaxy/zbus" target="_blank">zbus</a>, which is essentially the underlying library for nmrs.
  </p>

  <p>
    i love talking about the work i'm doing (or really anything else revolving around OSS) so if you'd like to chat, please reach out! i've left a list of my socials below.
    <ul>
      <li>email: <a href="mailto:alhakimiakrmj@gmail.com">alhakimiakrmj@gmail.com</a></li>
      <li>matrix: <a href="https://app.element.io/#/room/#zbus:matrix.org">@cachebag:matrix.org</a></li>
      <li>x(twitter): <a href="https://x.com/cachebagged">cachebagged</a></li>
      <li>linkedin: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/akrmalhakimi/">akrm al-hakimi</a></li>
    </ul>
  </p>

  <p>
    i've also left a list of my projects below.
  </p>

  <h2>projects</h2>
  <ul>
    {projects.map(project => (
      <li>
        <a href={project.url} target="_blank">{project.name}</a> &mdash; {project.description}
        {project.image && (
          <a href={project.url} target="_blank" class="thumb">
            <img src={project.image} alt={project.name} />
          </a>
        )}
      </li>
    ))}
  </ul>

  <h2>other</h2>
  <ul>
    {contributions.map(item => (
      <li>
        <a href={item.url} target="_blank">{item.name}</a> &mdash; {item.description}
        {item.image && (
          <a href={item.url} target="_blank" class="thumb">
            <img src={item.image} alt={item.name} />
          </a>
        )}
      </li>
    ))}
  </ul>
</Layout>

<style>
  .thumb {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.35rem;
  }

  .thumb img {
    width: 280px;
    height: 140px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: top left;
    border: 1px solid #333;
    border-radius: 3px;
    display: block;
  }
</style>
